<p>
    This is the .NET Core 6 version of the Sample MVC Web Application, demonstrating the migration 
    of the HomeController from ASP.NET MVC 5 (.NET Framework 4.5.1) to .NET Core 6.
</p>

<h3>Key Migration Changes:</h3>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Namespace:</strong> Changed from <code>System.Web.Mvc</code> to <code>Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc</code></li>
    <li><strong>Return Types:</strong> Updated from <code>ActionResult</code> to <code>IActionResult</code></li>
    <li><strong>Memory Metrics:</strong> Updated InternalsInfo model to use .NET Core compatible APIs</li>
    <li><strong>Views:</strong> Updated to use tag helpers and .NET Core conventions</li>
    <li><strong>Project Structure:</strong> Created new .NET Core 6 project with modern conventions</li>
</ul>
